1.description:
&lt;p&gt;It used to be that if you wanted to give users of your themes a way to customize aspects of their site or the theme, you&#x27;d create a theme options page. But now the best way (and the expected method for themes submitted to the theme directory) is to make use of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/advanced-topics/customizer-api/&quot;&gt;Customizer&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this tutorial, I&#x27;ll show you how to add Customizer functionality to your theme. We&#x27;ll cover:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An overview of the Customizer and its default settings,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The hooks and functions you need to use to interact with the Customizer,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adding sections to the Customizer,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adding controls to your sections, including color, text and radio buttons, and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing user inputs in your theme with settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#x27;ll also look at how you can let your users add text to their site and also how they can amend the styling by using a color picker in the Customizer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&#x27;s begin.&lt;/p&gt;

3.description:
&lt;p&gt;For each unit in this course, you are required to complete a multiple choice quiz based on the concepts you have learned about in the tutorial and video. You need to achieve an 80% score in order to pass and move on to the next unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you find the quiz tough, it&#x27;s because we&#x27;ve made it deliberately challenging – we want you to think about what you&#x27;ve learned (and really earn the certificate at the end of the course!). Each question is based on what&#x27;s been covered in the course material so if you&#x27;ve paid attention you should have no problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good luck&lt;/p&gt;

