1.description:
&lt;p&gt;Plugins let you add or change how your sites looks or functions. And the best part? Just about any kind of functionality you can dream up for your site, you can turn into a plugin and make it happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should already know how to create a basic plugin – if you don&#x27;t, you should review our &lt;a href=&quot;https://premium.wpmudev.org/academy/courses/wordpress-development-for-beginners-3&quot;&gt;WordPress Development for Beginners course&lt;/a&gt; before proceeding – so I&#x27;m not going to show you how to do that. Instead, we&#x27;ll look at how to build some more complex plugins as well as best practice for plugin development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So far in this course, you&#x27;ve developed a theme, including template files, hooks and Customizer functionality. In this part of the course, we&#x27;ll make use of one of the hooks you&#x27;ve already added, and insert content by hooking into it.&lt;/p&gt;
